From the “Where are they now” files ...Tim McTyer takes great pride that many consider BYU’s 14-1 1996 Cotton Bowl team to be the best defensive team the Cougars ever put on the field.
McTyer, who coaches high school football in Victorville, California, still keeps in contact with Morgan, who works at a store in Los Angeles near where he grew up.
“Margin and I talk a lot about training and things.”The Cotton Bowl win means a lot to McTyer.
“BYU was known as an offensive school and we tried to make it a defensive school.
In that 1996 season, McTyer led the team in pass breakups with 18.